Package com.brianmearns.crafter

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Builder<T>
    A Builder implements the builder design pattern, in which one object is used to construct instances of a particular type, after being setup step by step with values to transfer to the built instance.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ListBuilder<T>
    A Builder for a list of values.
    ListBuilder.DefaultListBuilder<T>  
    ListBuilder.NeverListBuilder<T>
    A ListBuilder which doesn't actually do anything.
    MapBuilder<K,V>  
    MapBuilder.DefaultMapBuilder<K,V>  
    ValueBuilder<T>
    A simple Builder for a single value.
    ValueBuilder.ValueBuilderOfBuilderFunction<T>
    A function that maps any builder of a value to a ValueBuilder of that builder.
    ValueBuilder.ValueBuilderOfInstanceFunction<T>
    A function that maps any value to a ValueBuilder of that instance.
